      • assertOptionallyThrowsUnsupportedOperationException

        public static void assertOptionallyThrowsUnsupportedOperationException(Runnable action)
        Asserts that an action either succeeds or throws an UnsupportedOperationException. This can be used to test operations on unmodifiable collections that will not throw any exception if the collection is not actually updated.
        Parameters:
        action - The action to run.

      • assertThrowsUnsupportedOperationExceptionOr

        public static void assertThrowsUnsupportedOperationExceptionOr(Class<? extends Exception> otherExpectedType,
                                                               Runnable action)
        Asserts that an action throws an UnsupportedOperationException or another type of exception. This can be used to test operations on unmodifiable collections that may throw another type of exception, such as NullPointerException.
        Parameters:
        otherExpectedType - The other possible expected exception type.
        action - The action to run.

      • assertThrowsUnsupportedOperationExceptionOr

        public static void assertThrowsUnsupportedOperationExceptionOr(org.hamcrest.Matcher<? super Exception> otherExpectedMatcher,
                                                               Runnable action)
        Asserts that an action throws an UnsupportedOperationException or another possible exception. This can be used to test operations on unmodifiable collections that may throw another possible exception.
        Parameters:
        otherExpectedMatcher - An alternative matcher for the expected exception type.
        action - The action to run.
